The graph of the rational function $\frac{p(x)}{q(x)}$ is shown below, with a horizontal asymptote at $y = 0$. If $q(x)$ is quadratic, $p(2)=2$, and $q(-1) = 18$, find $p(x) + q(x).$
[asy]
size(8cm);
import graph;

Label f; 
f.p=fontsize(6); 

real f(real x) {return 2*(x-1)/(3*(x-2)*(x-1));}

int gridsize = 5;
draw((-gridsize,0)--(gridsize,0), black+1bp, Arrows(8));
