From 30-60-90 triangle $ABD$, we have $BD = AB/2 = 10$.  From 45-45-90 triangle $BCD$, we have $BC = BD\sqrt{2} = \boxed{10\sqrt{2}}$.

Since $\angle ABC = \angle ADC = 90^\circ,$ $\overline{AC}$ must be a diameter of this circle.

[asy]
