There are a total of  \[36=2x+x+4x+2x=9x\]people on the team, so $x=4$.  We are trying to find the number of right-handed boys.  This number is  \[4x=4\cdot4=\boxed{16}.\]

We can rephrase the problem as the system of equations: \begin{align*}
\frac{a+2b}{2} &= 7\\
\frac{a+2c}{2} &= 8
\end{align*} Adding these gives: \begin{align*}
\frac{a+2b}{2}+\frac{a+2c}{2} &= 7+8\\
\frac{2a+2b+2c}{2} &= 15\\
a+b+c &= 15\\
\frac{a+b+c}{3} &= \frac{15}{3} = \boxed{5}
\end{align*}

[asy]
pair L,M,N;
N = (0,0);
M = (2,0);
