solution:
Since 3 of the 20 boxes have neither pens nor pencils, $20-3=17$ of them have pens, pencils, or both.  Let there be $x$ boxes with both.  As shown below, there are $13-x$ with pencils and $9-x$ with pens, so we must have $(13-x) + x + (9-x) = 17$.  Simplifying gives $22-x = 17$, so $x=\boxed{5}$.


